Content:
My favorite language is JavaScript too, and the most annoying wart for me is function scope instead of lexical scope. For example,<p><pre><code>    var closures = [];
    for (var i = 0; i < 10; i++)
    {
        var j = i;
        closures[i] = function() { alert(j); }
    }
    closures[0](); // outputs 9, WTF?
</code></pre>
How to fix it:<p><pre><code>    var closures = [];
    for (var i = 0; i < 10; i++) (function()
    {
        var j = i*i;
        closures[i] = function() { alert(j); }
    })(i)
    closures[0](); // outputs 0 as it should</code></pre>
